{"body": "If it's in the Content-Type header, there's no reason to put it in the HTML body other than the fact that it's easier to spot if you view the source.\r\n\r\nBesides, if we were to include the charset meta tag, it should come before the title tag, since the title could contain non-ASCII characters. I also believe that Rails sets the header dynamically, so if you use a different encoding than UTF-8 it will correctly set that too.", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/2645013", "created_at": "2011-11-06T11:54:14Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/3539#issuecomment-2645013", "updated_at": "2011-11-06T11:54:14Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 3539, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/henrikhodne/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/henrikhodne/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/henrikhodne/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/henrikhodne", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/henrikhodne/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/henrikhodne", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/henrikhodne/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/d036be96167a38393d657c66a25ec85c?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2Ff1ab4591a72bfca2da721ca61a6e9569.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/henrikhodne/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/henrikhodne/received_events", "gravatar_id": "d036be96167a38393d657c66a25ec85c", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/henrikhodne/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "henrikhodne", "type": "User", "id": 24421, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/henrikhodne/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "52383522bd3543c15100fbe3"}, "id": 2645013, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/3539"}
